SOURCE: https://github.com/jsx-eslint/eslint-plugin-react/blob/master/docs/rules/jsx-key.md#2025-04-14_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
<span {...spread} key={"key-after-spread"} />;
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Incorrect JSX Bracket Spacing Examples with 'afterOpening: always'
DESCRIPTION: Examples of JSX code that violate the 'afterOpening: always' rule, which requires a space after the opening bracket of JSX elements.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jsx-eslint/eslint-plugin-react/blob/master/docs/rules/jsx-tag-spacing.md#2025-04-14_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
<Hello></Hello>
<Hello firstname="John"/>
<Hello
  firstName="John"
  lastName="Smith"
/>
```

