TITLE: Incorrect JSX Spacing Examples with 'always' Option
DESCRIPTION: Examples of JSX code that violate the 'react/jsx-equals-spacing' rule when configured with the 'always' option. These examples show incorrect spacing around equal signs in JSX attributes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jsx-eslint/eslint-plugin-react/blob/master/docs/rules/jsx-equals-spacing.md#2025-04-14_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
<Hello name={firstname} />;
<Hello name ={firstname} />;
<Hello name= {firstname} />;
```

